Package com.frc5113.library.drivers

Class PhotonLED

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.frc5113.library.drivers.PhotonLED
  • public class PhotonLED
extends java.lang.Object
    Used to command a Teensy running the photon LED control library. Commands the Photon library are just strings of comma seperated numbers with a semicolon at the end 2 = SetAnimation= 2, StripNumber, Animation, Color1, Color2, rate, fade; You can leave off values and defaults will be set for the rest of the values 3 = SetNumberOfLeds = 3, StripNumber, NumberOfLEDsInStrip Color Chart = Red (0..) Orange (32..) Yellow (64..) Green (96..) Aqua (128..) Blue (160..) Purple (192..) Pink(224..) White(255) - This isn't normally on the HUE chart but used in this library to make animaitons easier
